behind your house, right?

74
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:24,400
So why the heck did I have
to wait three days for you

75
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:25,133
to show?

76
00:05:34,566 --> 00:05:35,933
-Don't patronize me!

77
00:05:36,033 --> 00:05:37,300
Do you think I
was just strolling

78
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:39,166
around Japan for my health?

79
00:05:39,266 --> 00:05:41,000
-So what were you doing?

80
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:45,033
-Listen, you have absolutely no
idea the troubles I've endured.

81
00:05:47,366 --> 00:05:51,233
Ranma Saotome, today is
the day I shall break you!

82
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:04,766
-What?

83
00:06:04,866 --> 00:06:06,033
No, this is Enoshima.

84
00:06:07,066 --> 00:06:08,266
-No, you idiot, this is Asaksa.

85
00:06:08,366 --> 00:06:09,533
Can't you read a map?

86
00:06:10,966 --> 00:06:13,566
-Where did they move
that cursed lot?

87
00:06:13,666 --> 00:06:14,700
-What are you, nuts?

88
00:06:17,133 --> 00:06:19,000
-You gotta be kidding,
this is Yokohama.

89
00:06:21,566 --> 00:06:25,900
--[panting] I finally--
I fi-- finally made it--

90
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:26,900
finally made it.

91
00:06:29,966 --> 00:06:31,600
Damn you, Ranma Saotome!

92
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:32,566
You coward!

93
00:06:34,066 --> 00:06:36,833
[sigh]

94
00:06:36,933 --> 00:06:39,000
RYOGA (VOICEOVER): And that
wasn't the worst of it.

95
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:41,466
Not only does he blow
off my challenge,

96
00:06:41,566 --> 00:06:42,966
he goes running to China.

97
00:06:43,066 --> 00:06:46,833
And then me, stupid me, like
a moron goes off chasing him.

98
00:06:46,933 --> 00:06:49,200
Oh, that was when the
real tragedy started.

99
00:06:50,533 --> 00:06:52,433
Oh, if only I'd known.

100
00:06:54,133 --> 00:06:56,666
