101
00:06:56,766 --> 00:07:00,133
-[bumbling sounds]

102
00:07:00,233 --> 00:07:02,600
-Wait up, you fool.

103
00:07:02,700 --> 00:07:03,600
Kiai!

104
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:05,100
-[screaming]

105
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:08,066
-[bumbling sounds]

106
00:07:08,166 --> 00:07:09,033
-Come back here!

107
00:07:09,133 --> 00:07:11,033
Come back here!

108
00:07:11,133 --> 00:07:13,000
-[screaming]

109
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:19,666
Some crazy girl had
knocked me off the cliff

110
00:07:19,766 --> 00:07:21,266
and straight into the lake.

111
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:28,033
And then, that's when I--
that's when I realized that--

112
00:07:28,133 --> 00:07:30,433
-[squealing]

113
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:36,500
-I'd been cast into hell.

114
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:38,600
-[squealing]

115
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:41,300
-[bumbling and squealing]

116
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:51,600
-Oh, sir.

117
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:54,333
You find too, too
delicious piglet.

118
00:07:54,433 --> 00:07:55,100
Looks very juicy.

119
00:07:56,733 --> 00:08:00,100
I make famous Cantonese style
sweet and sour pork for you.

120
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:04,766
-[squealing]

121
00:08:04,866 --> 00:08:08,200
-See here, [inaudible],
they're very famous,

122
00:08:08,300 --> 00:08:10,300
very cursed spring
called [inaudible].

123
00:08:11,566 --> 00:08:17,166
-[blowing]

124
00:08:17,266 --> 00:08:19,766
-[squealing]

125
00:08:19,866 --> 00:08:22,600
-There very tragic legend
of piglet that drowned

126
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:25,766
there 1,200 year ago.

127
00:08:25,866 --> 00:08:28,133
Oh, very terrible legend, sir.

128
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:31,000
Now whoever fall in spring
take a body of black piglet.

129
00:08:33,433 --> 00:08:36,066
I think maybe this one come
from cursed Jusenkyo spring

130
00:08:36,166 --> 00:08:37,500
drowned black piglet.

131
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,866
No?

132
00:08:38,966 --> 00:08:40,633
Ah, sir, you hear?

133
00:08:40,733 --> 00:08:42,166
I make a funny joke, no?

134
00:08:42,266 --> 00:08:43,933
[laughter]

135
00:08:44,033 --> 00:08:46,200
-[squealing]

136
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:47,566
-[screaming] Hot!

137
00:08:47,666 --> 00:08:48,107
Hot!

138
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:48,607
Hot!

139
00:08:48,666 --> 00:08:49,466
Hot!

140
00:08:49,566 --> 00:08:51,133
-You human, not pig.

141
00:08:51,233 --> 00:08:52,533
No can eat this one.

142
00:08:52,633 --> 00:08:55,600
-Just the thought of it makes
me so angry I want to kill him.

143
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:58,266
Ranma, you are so dead.

144
00:08:58,366 --> 00:08:59,066
MAN 1: Runaway pig!

145
00:09:00,633 --> 00:09:02,466
PIG: [squealing]

146
00:09:02,566 --> 00:09:03,433
MAN 2: [inaudible].

147
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:08,300
MAN 3: I thought
we'd never catch him.

148
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,766
MAN 2: Don't let him get away!

149
00:09:12,300 --> 00:09:14,133
Here, pig, pig pig, pig!

150
00:09:14,233 --> 00:09:15,466
Come here, pig!

151
00:09:15,566 --> 00:09:16,007
-Pig!

152
00:09:16,066 --> 00:09:16,507
Pig!

153
00:09:16,566 --> 00:09:17,733
Pig!

154
00:09:17,833 --> 00:09:20,866
Would you quit it
with the pig already?

155
00:09:20,966 --> 00:09:23,766
-[squealing]

156
00:09:31,566 --> 00:09:32,100
[squeal]

157
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:33,566
-[squeal]

158
00:09:33,666 --> 00:09:37,000
-[squeal]

159
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:38,000
-[squeal]

160
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:40,433
MAN 2: It's in here!

161
00:09:40,533 --> 00:09:41,933
MAN 1: I'll watch this door.

162
00:09:42,033 --> 00:09:44,533
You two go around the back.

163
00:09:44,633 --> 00:09:45,074
OK?

164
00:09:46,866 --> 00:09:47,800
-[scream] Hot!

165
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:48,341
Hot!

166
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:48,841
Hot!

167
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:51,266
-Who are you?

168
00:09:51,366 --> 00:09:52,200
-What's the matter?

169
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:53,666
That-- that fellow
yelled so loud,

170
00:09:53,766 --> 00:09:55,566
I thought he was being
murdered or something.

171
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:59,666
-That was maybe just
a little too hot.

172
00:09:59,766 --> 00:10:01,000
-Man, who the heck are you?

173
00:10:02,433 --> 00:10:05,900
-I kind of got lost and I
thought I'd spend the night.

174
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,233
Why do you ask?

175
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:09,966
MAN 1: Oh, well, uh, heck of
a storm out there, ain't it?

176
00:10:10,066 --> 00:10:11,066
Why, I never seen a--

177
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:12,033
-Get to the point!

178
00:10:12,133 --> 00:10:13,900
